Citations
Date:  0/0/1941
Source:  NZ Slang
Author:  BAKER
Vol / Page:  39
Edition:
Quote:  When flocks are mixed they are said to be <i>boxed</i>, and from this peculiar use of the verb we have derived the term a <i>box-up</i>, a state of confusion, and <i>to be in a box</i>, to be in a confused state of mind.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1988
Source:  Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author:  McGILL
Vol / Page:  20
Edition:
Quote:   <i>box up</i> state of confusion; eg `It's a total box up, nobody seems to know what his position is, or what he's s'posed to do.' ANZ.
